{
  "texts": [
    "Each edge consists of two nodes and the timestamp indicates the time of its generation.",
    "The two most frequently occurring patterns in the stream are the \"star\" and \"path\" structures.",
    "The \"star\" structure branches out into multiple paths, while the \"path\" structure follows a single propagation path within a subgraph.",
    "The model identifies a group of patterns by considering both behavioral and structural features for stance classification over subgraphs.",
    "Lastly, the sequence of graph snapshots over time is recursively integrated to reconstruct the structure, enabling the differentiation between rumors and non-rumors."
  ]
}